The paper focuses on studying the influence of web communities on each other through the lens of mainstream and alternative news sources. This involves analyzing millions of posts on Twitter, Reddit, and 4chan, and measuring how news flows between these platforms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
